snippet.textDisplay: Riverdale to everyone is like Family Guy to me. The show started off actually good and felt like it was worth watching. Over the years, Family Guy was slowly descending to where they are now -- which is not at all funny and quite a bit offensive, and just something you think should have ended a long time ago. Riverdale is much like that. No, I in fact don't like this show and have no intention of ever watching it (just not my taste of TV, honestly.) But what I think makes people keep watching is because of the investment of time; you took the time to watch, probably binge, the first season so you invested many hours of that show. So you go in to the next season and from I heard took a 180 in the wrong direction, but because you already took the time to watch the previous season you force yourself to keep watching. That's Family Guy for me, the show itself isn't good anymore but given how much time given the show to actually sit down and watch, giving up on it now wouldn't really do anything (probably saves my brain cells lol) but I think that's why people are still watching Riverdale despite how completely obscure it's become.
